id: pm-u2tm
title: Describe --markdown writes reference docs to a file
description: "Follow-up to pm-dmum: add an agent-friendly --output path for pm extension/package describe --markdown so package authors can generate README/reference docs directly from the single source of truth without shell redirection. Duplicate check: pm search 'describe markdown output file renderExtensionSurfaceMarkdown write README reference' --status all found pm-dmum as the closed parent surface but no file-output implementation item."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:extensions","area:packages","area:sdk"
created_at: "2026-06-25T20:24:56.707Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-25T21:03:00.215Z"
author: codex-gpt5
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Implemented --output for package/extension describe Markdown generation with contract, completion, docs, fixture, and regression coverage."
expected_result: pm package/extension describe --markdown can write deterministic reference Markdown directly to a requested file path without stdout duplication and remains discoverable through SDK contracts/completions.
actual_result: "CLI writes Markdown to the requested file, creates parent directories, supports quiet output, rejects invalid --output usage before dispatch, and SDK contracts/completions/docs advertise the flag."
